What is Cloud watch?
--------------------
-It helps you see the health and performance of your infrastructure

What it monitors:
-----------------
-EC2 : CPU, Memory , disk , network
when ever the CPU > 80% of EC2 instance you will trigger alarm from cloud watch and get notification from SNS.

Definition:
Cloud watch is a monitoring and observability service
It collects metrics, logs and event from AWS resources and applications and 
lets you:
  -Monitor performance
  -Set alarms
  -Troubleshoot issues
  -View dash boards

Key fatures:
-------------
1.Metrics: collects utilization (EC2, CPU usage, disk I/O, memory, network
2.Logs: collects data from application
3.Alarms: Trigger actions when metrics across the threshold
Example: If CPU > 80% for minutues ----> send alert or stop/start an instance.


Demo:
If CPU on an EC2 server goes above 85%:
-Cloudwatch alarm triggers
-Sends notification through SNS
-Can trigger Autoscaling or restat actions

Note:
Cloud watch is monitoring service usedf to collect metrics, logs, set alarms and automate actions for cloud resources and applications











